The paper deals with the analysis of large-scale heterogeneous datasets capturing online user interactions and behaviors, which is a common topic in the field of social computing. The proposed Constrained Latent Space Model (CLSM) combines Mixed Membership Stochastic Blockmodels (MMSB) and Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) to jointly model social interactions and user attributes/behaviors. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SD (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). Among these, cs.SI is the most likely category as it directly relates to the study of social networks and their properties.
